results.task_name: Break down a feature into tasks
results.prompt_sent: I need to implement user notifications for workunit updates. Think about what steps are actually needed to build this end-to-end, then create a workunit called "Implement User Notifications" and add all the implementation tasks to it. Be thorough — this is a real feature, not a toy example.

arguments.name: Implement User Notifications
arguments.problem_statement: Design and implement a user notification system that alerts users to workunit updates (status changes, task assignments, comments, etc.) via multiple channels while allowing users to control their notification preferences.
arguments.success_criteria:
- Users receive real-time notifications when workunits they own/contribute to are updated
- Users can customize notification preferences (channels, frequency, specific event types)
- Notifications include relevant context about the update
- System scales to support enterprise-level user volume
- All notifications are auditable and retrievable by users
- Notifications integrate with existing authentication system
arguments.description: A comprehensive implementation of user notification functionality for workunit updates, including backend services, frontend components, and user preference management.
